        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=ICQ&ICQ=9112261&M_NAME=Veritos')"><img src="http://online.mirabilis.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=9112261&img=5" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Veritos an ICQ Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=AIM&AIM=melkor486   melkor350&M_NAME=Veritos')"><img src="icon_aim.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Veritos an instant message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=39008&TOPIC_ID=5199&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Epic+Spells%21%21&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Guys, look.  The necro is screwed up.  I love my necro.  He's 24.  I haven't played him since someone demanded of me that I give them my mana.  He's been 24 for nearly 3 months now and most of his gear is currently on a mage I created.  There are times I miss him.  Times I want to play him again.  Then I remember the resists.  I mean, at least as a mage I get a PARTIAL resist.  Not just an outright "<target> has resisted your darkness spell".  I mean, just look at the darkness line for instance.  With every other class, an upgraded spell means a spell that is more powerfull and more effective than their previous one.  With ours, it's just a sign that our prior series of spells might actually stick.  Ya know, I wasn't able to get our lvl 16 Engulfing Darkness to actually stick on anything I was fighting (save for those significantly lower than me) until I was lvl 21!  That alone put a VERY bad taste in my mouth.  And from everything I have read here and everything I have heard from other high level necro's....it only gets worse.  Verant has taken a very powerfull class, one I would say was on the boarder, if not actually was, overpowered....and nerfed them to the point of near uselessness.  A necro should SHINE on long BIG fights.  Instead, the very fights that seemed to have been made with a necro in mind (the one's where the dots actually do full damage), the necro spells are resisted OUTRIGHT, if not WORSE. (I.E. corpse poofage.)  The epic, sucks.  Compared to the epics of the other classes, it's pretty pathetic.  I mean, take the mage's or the cleric's!  The mage gets an UBER of uber pets...FREE.  He summons an orb (not no-rent) and the orb (which is itself a decent 1hb weapon) summons the pet with a simple click.  The Cleric gets free MANALESS rezzes!  What's a necro get?  A combat spell that takes 9 seconds to cast and is probably going to be resisted anyway!</P><P>I'm sorry.. I don't ask for much and I am usually not one to speak unless I see an blatent problem.  Necro's don't want to be "uber" again.  (Granted, it would be nice to command authority and respect simply for being a necro...but that's not the point.)  I mean, I have read all the class talk threads and everything and the one blaring thing I have heard again and again and again is this..  "Make us usefull again."  I mean, lets not kid ourselves here.  No matter what verant wants us to believe.  The "reward" for playing a char to high level is the ability to go to the planes or fight "uber" mobs and get some of the most amazing gear availibe in the game.  Yet, in those very encounters we are reduced to little more than walking mana batteries...and not very good ones at that.  I mean, we're not even coveted for our ability to summon corpses any more.  Yes, there is more to the game than the "uber" encounters, but I am not playing the game simply so I can say "I went to sebilis".  I am playing the game so I can say "I went to Fear and KILLED Cazic himself!".  I'm sorry, but we're broke...  We need fixed, at least REPAIRED before any new "epic" things are added.</P><P>Fear.<BR>Fear attracts the Fearfull,<BR>The Strong,<BR>The Weak,<BR>The Innocent.<BR>Fear is my Ally.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

